result.execSummary:
The defendant Kendall L Simmons was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • 2nd Degree Sexual Assault/Use of Force [Modifiers: Party to a Crime], a class C felony, Wisconsin Statutes 940.225(2)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

*Index re-submitted after Supreme Court Order dated 1/21/2020.

Per Order dated January 21, 2020, Appeal No. 2017AP2163-CR, 
IT IS ORDERED that, consistent with the court's December 16, 2019 order, the clerk of this court shall, within ten business days of the date of this order, unseal the record in this case in its entirety, as well as all filings in this court and the court of appeals, except for those documents identified in the parties' December 30, 2019 joint report. 
IT IS FURTHER ORDERED that, consistent with the court's December 16, 2019 order, upon the unsealing of the record, the clerk shall: 1) provide standard docket information regarding this matter on both the Wisconsin Circuit Court Access Program website and the Wisconsin Supreme Court and Court of appeals Case Access website; and 2) amend the caption by substituting defendant-appellant-petitioner's real name as defendant-appellant-petitioner in this matter, and by including the circuit court case number associated with this appeal, as is the normal course.  
IT IS FURTHER ORDERED that the court will consider the pending petititon for review in due course. 
Patience Drake Roggensack, C.J. (dissenting).  I dissent for the reasons given in my dissent to the court's December 16, 2019 order in this case.  I am authorized to state that Justice Annette Kingsland Ziegler joins this dissent.
Per Supreme Court of Wisconsin notice dated January 21, 2020, citing December 16, 2019 order.

Per order dated December 16, 2019, Appeal No. 2017AP2163-CR, IT IS ORDERED that the defendant-appellant-petitioner's "Motion to Seal and Proceed Under Modified Caption" is denied.  The clerk of this court shall unseal the record in this case in its entirety, as well as all filings in this court and the court of appeals, except for those documents that are commonly restricted from public access because they are protected by law (e.g., presentence investigation reports) or because they disclose information that is commonly recognized as sensitive and confidential (e.g., physical or mental health information, crime victim information, etc.).  The parties shall provide a joint report listing all such documents within fourteen days of the date of this order.  

IT IS FURTHER ORDERED that, upon the unsealing of the record, the clerk shall provide standard docket information regarding this matter on both the CCAP and WSCCA websites.  Also at that time, the clerk shall amend the caption by substituting defendant-appellant-petitioner's real name as defendant-appellant-petitioner in this matter, and by including the circuit court case number associated with this appeal, as is the normal course.  

IT IS FURTHER ORDERED that the court will consider the pending petition for review in due course.  

PATIENCE DRAKE ROGGENSACK, C.J. (dissenting).  I would grant defendant-appellant-petitioner's "Motion to Seal and Proceed Under Modified Capton," or, at a minimum, would remand this matter to the circuit court to allow defendant-appellant-petitioner the opportunity to further develop the record regarding the need for the requested confidentiality accomidations.  

I am authorized to state that Justice ANNETTE KINGSLAND ZIEGLER joins this dissent.  

REBECCA FRANK DALLET, J. (dissenting).  I would hold defendant-appellant-petitioner's "Motion to Seal and Proceed Under Modified Caption" in abeyance, and remand this matter to the circuit court to allow defendant-appellant-petitioner the opportunity to further develop the record regarding the need for the requested confidentiality accomodations.

Per order dated October 17, 2019, Appeal No. 2017AP2163-CR, IT IS ORDERED that the defendant-appellant-petitioner show cause, in writing, why the circuit court record, the appellate filings, and the circuit court and appellate dockets should not be unsealed, and the caption amended to include the defendant-appeallant-petitioner's real name and the circuit court case number.  The response to this order must: (1) specify what documents, if any, are proposed to be sealed or redacted; (2) specify what modifications, if any, must be made to the entries appearing on the circuit court and appellate dockets so as to allow these dockets to be made publicly accesible; and (3) specify the factual basis in the record and the legal authority for each such requested seal, redaction, or docket entry modification, as well as for the continued use of the pseudonym "John Doe" in place of the defendant-appellant-petitioner's real name and the omission of the circuit courts case number from the case caption.  Defendant-appellant-petitioner shall file this response within fourteen days from the date of this order. Within seven calendar days of the filing of the response, the state shall file a reply stating its objections to, or agreement with, the response.

IT IS FURTHER ORDERED that the defendant-appellant-petitioner's "Motion To Seal And Proceed Under Modified Caption" will be held in abeyance pending further order of the court.

IT IS FURTHER ORDERED that the defendant-appellant-petitioner's petition for review and accompanying appendix will be held under seal during the pendency of the "Motion To Seal And Proceed Under Modified Caption"

IT IS FURTHER ORDERED that the clerk of court shall place both the "Motion To Seal And Proceed Under Modified Caption" and this order in the public court file in this matter.  PATIENCE DRAKE ROGGENSACK,C.J., and ANNETTE K. ZIEGLER J., dissent.
